{"body": "I don't think this is incorrect behavior - the sql generated is literally what the where statement says. If I ask for a query that returns the empty set, I don't expect an ActiveRecord::StatementInvalid to be raised.\r\n\r\nThere are many situations where this might occur. Consider:\r\n\r\nPosts.where(author: Author.new_since(1.day.ago))\r\n\r\nIf no new authors have signed up since a day ago, this should not return an error - there's simply no posts to be displayed.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/13269185", "created_at": "2013-02-07T23:42:04Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9216#issuecomment-13269185", "updated_at": "2013-02-07T23:42:04Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9216, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jaggederest", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/69c54cc530fa953e144771c03eccc5a9?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff11bec1411101c743f64df596773d0b2.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/received_events", "gravatar_id": "69c54cc530fa953e144771c03eccc5a9", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jaggederest", "type": "User", "id": 3559, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jaggederest/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523d41dabd354364b9005b7d"}, "id": 13269185, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9216"}
